  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.6.1\r\nOS & Version: OS & Version: windows 10 (64 bits)   - Linux Mint 18.1 (Xfce - 64 bits)\r\n\r\n_______________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\nHello,\r\nI use Geth (with Mist 0.8.10) .... and I appreciate it so much...\r\nI use Geth on my Windows 10 PC (192.168.0.1) and it works very well (blockchain OK and synced)...\r\nbut now I have a new Linux PC on my local network (192.168.0.2)... and I'd like to use Geth/Mist also on this new PC (to use MultiSig...) ... but this new PC has a slow HDD and I can't download blockchain on this new PC.\r\nIs there a concrete way to connect this Linux PC to my Windows 10 PC (192.168.0.1) to use only one blockchain (node?) ?\r\nWhat is the correct CLI command and options (rpc or ipc options???) to use to connect to an other blockchain?\r\nThanks in advance for your answer.\r\n",
